(326431, 494, 10320, 'masood357', 4098, '', 1355249148, 'Two guys go hunting. Jerry has never gone hunting while Joe has hunted all his life. When they get to the northern Wisconsin woods, Joe tells Jerry to sit by a tree and not make a sound while Joe checks out a deer stand. After he gets about a quarter of a mile away, Joe hears a blood-curdling scream. He rushes back to Jerry and yells, "I thought I told you to be quiet!" Jerry says, "Hey, I tried. I really did. When those snakes crawled over me, I didn''t make a sound. When that bear was breathing down my neck, I didn''t make a peep. But when those two chipmunks crawled up my pants leg and said, ''Should we take them with us or eat them here?'' I couldn''t keep quiet any more!"', 1, 0, '115.186.115.97', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 0, 0),
