(332232, 10648, 0, 'MHMalik', 801, 'Effect of &quot;Netting&quot; on Hunting', 1357302717, 'Dear Fellow Members,\r\n\r\nI would like to know your esteemed opinion regarding the negative effects of "netting" (for lack of better term in my limited vocabulary) on Shikar, particularly of upland birds. There are laws regarding the number of birds one can shoot, but one net (with the tape recorder) can wreak havoc with the local bird population in the immediate area. I think conservationists should focus more on prohibiting such inhumane activity rather than on banning autoloader shotguns and such like policies. After all, how many birds can one take down in a day if you are giving the bird a fair chance to take flying shots.\r\n\r\nAlso, what are your kind opinions on the ETHICAL number of birds hunted? Personally I think one should only shoot enough to cater to the meal of the hunting party and some spare change, and not devastate the entire populace. \r\n\r\nSince we are responsible members, I think we should also undertake efforts to restore the population numbers of the game, else our children will have nothing left at this rate. \r\n\r\nComments/Opinions?', 1, 1, '182.177.196.231', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 0, 0),
